        "text": "the wood devoured more",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", &c.] The explanation generally given is that they perished in the pits and precipices and morasses of the forest: but this seems unlikely. More probably it means that owing to the nature of the ground more were slain in the pursuit through the forest, than in the actual battle.",
        "children": []
